To summarize where we landed after the Zulip discussion and some follow-up PRs:
- the PR #16103 added *native* support for cancellative semirings in `linear_combination`;
- the PR #16166 preserved (near-) backward compatibility (in particular the original syntax and the rudimentary support for non-cancellative semirings) by duplicating `linear_combination` to a tactic `linear_combination'` which will not be further modified.
